data.title: Tate Donovan Biography
data.meta_description: Read all about Tate Donovan with TV Guide's exclusive biography including their list of awards, celeb facts and more at TV Guide.
data.text:
Fast Facts

Plays the fiddle and the bodhran

Appeared on Friends in 1998 as a love interest for Rachel, played by his then-girlfriend, Jennifer Aniston

After both of his parents were diagnosed with bladder cancer, he became the national spokesperson for the Bladder Cancer Advocacy Network

His mother recovered, but his father succumbed to the disease in 2001

Has volunteered with the Young Storytellers program, a group that works with children writing their own screenplays

Began honing his directing skills while he was a cast member on The O

C

His director credits include episodes of the television shows Glee and Damages
